docs.abstract: Joe Biden said his administration would administer 200 million vaccines by April 30.
docs.snippet: Joe Biden said his administration would administer 200 million vaccines by April 30.
docs.lead_paragraph: Joe Biden held his first presidential news conference this afternoon and announced a new goal: His administration would administer 200 million vaccines within his first 100 days in office, or April 30, double his initial goal.

docs.abstract: An analysis found that more than 2,334 adults were buried on Hart Island last year, up from 846 in 2019.
docs.snippet: An analysis found that more than 2,334 adults were buried on Hart Island last year, up from 846 in 2019.
docs.lead_paragraph: As many as one-tenth of the people who have died from the coronavirus in New York City may go unclaimed and be buried on Hart Island, the city’s potter’s field, according to an analysis of city data.

headline.main: Up to a tenth of New York City’s coronavirus dead may be buried in a potter’s field.

docs.abstract: The Vatican has been hit hard by the economic impact of the pandemic, prompting Francis to impose pay cuts on cardinals and others so lower-ranking employees can keep their jobs.
docs.snippet: The Vatican has been hit hard by the economic impact of the pandemic, prompting Francis to impose pay cuts on cardinals and others so lower-ranking employees can keep their jobs.
docs.lead_paragraph: ROME — In an effort to contain costs and save jobs amid a slump in tourist dollars and donations as a result of the coronavirus pandemic, Pope Francis has ordered across-the-board pay cuts for the cardinals and other higher-ranking clerics working in the Vatican.

headline.main: As Coronavirus Hits Vatican Revenue, Pope Cuts Pay for High-Ranking Clerics
headline.print_headline: Pope Cuts Pay for Top Clerics As Vatican Revenue Declines

docs.abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio said that the city would create a vaccination site for theater workers to try to help Broadway shows reopen by the fall.
docs.snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio said that the city would create a vaccination site for theater workers to try to help Broadway shows reopen by the fall.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio announced on Thursday that the city plans to create a coronavirus vaccination site on Broadway that will be reserved for theater industry workers, promising to dedicate city resources to help Broadway theaters reopen for live performances in the fall.

headline.main: Coming to Broadway: Vaccinations for New York’s Theater Workers

docs.abstract: The crisis in Papua New Guinea is a reminder that the virus will keep wreaking havoc until the whole world is vaccinated.
docs.snippet: The crisis in Papua New Guinea is a reminder that the virus will keep wreaking havoc until the whole world is vaccinated.
docs.lead_paragraph: The emergency rooms are heaving, health care workers are falling sick, and misinformation about the coronavirus is running rife. It has all left Papua New Guinea, an island nation just north of Australia, in the grip of a deadly crisis, as a tripling of infections over the past month has swamped an already fragile health care system.

headline.main: This Island Nation Had Zero Covid Cases for Months. Now It’s Overwhelmed.
headline.print_headline: Island’s Outbreak, After Zero Cases for Months

docs.abstract: The E.U. is preparing to curb vaccine exports for the next six weeks because of supply shortages.
docs.snippet: The E.U. is preparing to curb vaccine exports for the next six weeks because of supply shortages.
docs.lead_paragraph: The European Union is preparing to curb vaccine exports for the next six weeks in response to an acute supply shortage — just as a third wave of cases is taxing hospitals and sending country after country into lockdown.
